cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques applied to iris and periocular images for predicting gender and race. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves image processing and feature extraction, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of texture descriptors and machine learning algorithms for classification suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves statistical analysis and evaluation of the proposed method, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the proposed method on biometric systems and privacy concerns, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
